The reaction goes from SUM (RS, charge -3) to SUB (PS, charge -2) and from protonated to ionized GLU.
The charges for SUM and SUB that Aqvist used are force-field charges, and yet they are a little
different that the ffld_server charges that I obtained

For GLU and GLH, ffld_server charges are the same as in Aqvist's fep file.

In this library and topology I used Aqvist's charges
----------------
The dimer from Protein Data Bank had ID "1NEY"

